HEADWORD: Galantine
<hw>Gal"an*tine</hw> <pr>(? or ?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>galantine</ets>.]</ety> <def>A dish of veal, chickens, or other
white meat, freed from bones, tied up, boiled, and served cold.</def>
<rj><au>Smart.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
